    question: "Is Vaughan waterproofing covered by home insurance?",
    answer: "Home insurance in Vaughan typically covers sudden waterproofing failures (burst pipes, sewer backup with rider, sump pump failure if recent) but excludes gradual seepage, maintenance issues, and pre-existing conditions. Overland flood insurance (separate rider) covers Humber River flooding events but requires active prevention measures. Most insurers require proof of sump pump maintenance and working backwater valves. DrySpace provides detailed invoices and reports for insurance claims, documents emergency flood responses (90-minute response time), and can coordinate with adjusters. Waterproofing is considered preventative maintenance — investing in it may lower premiums."
  },
  {
    question: "When is the best season for waterproofing in Vaughan?",
    answer: "The best seasons for Vaughan waterproofing are late spring (May-June after frost) and early fall (September-October before freeze). Summer works but schedules fill quickly. Winter waterproofing (November-March) is possible with frost-depth excavation, heated tarps, and cold-weather membranes but adds 15-20% cost. Spring is ideal for addressing winter damage, fall for preparing before harsh weather. Emergency repairs happen year-round — DrySpace operates 24/7 with 90-minute response across all Vaughan neighborhoods. Book 4-6 weeks ahead in peak season, 2-3 weeks in winter."
